OL,3,CCouncil carers strike over
OL,4,C'outrageous' system where they had to
OL,5,C'work for free'
OL,7,FThe union says that despite this
OL,8,F"clearly being working time", staff
OL,9,Fwould then be classed as "in
OL,10,Fshortfall" of hours and were called in
OL,11,Fto work on their designated days off
OL,12,Fwith no pay.
OL,14,FRachael Sweetman is one of those
OL,15,Fstriking. She described the shortfall
OL,16,Fshift as being "unfair", adding: "Even
OL,17,Fif you only owed half an hour, you had
OL,18,Fto be available for either a three-and-
OL,19,Fa-half-hour shift or a five-hour shift.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
