OL,3,CCouncil carers strike over
OL,4,C'outrageous' system where they had to
OL,5,C'work for free'
OL,7,F"It was an extra day in the week where
OL,8,Fyou couldn't plan anything - you
OL,9,Fcouldn't do anything, you couldn't go
OL,10,Fanywhere - because you had to be
OL,11,Favailable."
OL,13,FThis practice is no longer in place
OL,14,Fbut the workers are striking in the
OL,15,Fhope of getting compensation for hours
OL,16,Fthey say they worked "for free".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/12
